WEBVTT

00:08.425 --> 00:11.678
If the millage does not pass,
we are losing bodies.

00:13.304 --> 00:16.140
They're projecting that
we're gonna lose at least 20 positions.

00:16.224 --> 00:18.560
Before this millage, the people were told

00:18.643 --> 00:23.106
they were gonna get a lot of new cops
and more safety on the streets.

00:23.857 --> 00:25.316
It's time to stand up and say,

00:25.400 --> 00:28.278
"We gave it to you last time
and we're still in the same boat."

00:28.361 --> 00:31.114
<i>Crime rate's high.</i>
<i>Police aren't showing up.</i>

00:31.197 --> 00:34.993
If you're not doing what you're supposed
to with the funding you already have,

00:35.076 --> 00:37.203
why should anyone give you more?

00:37.287 --> 00:42.041
If the millage does not pass, we will not
be able to support the staff that we have.

00:42.542 --> 00:45.253
Bridgette and I live together.
That's our income.

00:45.587 --> 00:47.464
<i>If it gets to me, it got to her already.</i>

00:47.547 --> 00:49.799
People are fed up. Everybody's broke.

00:49.883 --> 00:51.509
We must get this millage.

00:52.010 --> 00:54.179
I can't even imagine what I would do.

00:54.888 --> 00:56.556
It might not pass.

00:56.639 --> 01:01.102
[echoing clock ticking]

01:03.000 --> 01:09.074
